@startuml
title Component Diagram: NeoVex — Antigravity Agentic Integration into Neovim
' Version: 0.1.0 — update this diagram whenever the architecture changes

skinparam componentStyle uml2

[Neovim Editor] as Neovim <<Lightweight Editor>>
package "Neovim Extensions" {
  [Custom Plugin (Lua/Rust)] as NvimPlugin <<mlua interop>>
  [avante.nvim / opencode.nvim] as ExistingPlugins <<Proxy AI Workflows — Fallback>>
}

[Antigravity IDE] as AG <<VS Code Fork — Dev-time Only>>
note bottom of AG
  Used by both collaborators for research and implementation.
  Features: Multi-agent orchestration, Gemini 3 Pro, browser context.
  NOT required at runtime. NOT a local LLM (see Principle 11).
end note

package "Rust-Based Agentic Core (Principle 9)" {
  [Rust Agent Server] as RustServer <<axum + tokio — localhost:7777>>
  note right of RustServer
    Canonical crate stack:
    - rig: Agent pipelines
    - agentai: LLM integration
    - ADK-Rust: Modular agents
    - axum: HTTP server
    - tokio: Async runtime
    - mlua: Lua/Neovim interop
    This is the ORCHESTRATION layer.
    All inference routes to cloud (Principle 7).
  end note
}

[Gemini API] as Gemini <<Primary Cloud LLM — Cloud-First>>
note bottom of Gemini
  Primary inference layer (Principle 7).
  Accessed via API keys or Antigravity OAuth.
  Budget and quota tracked by model-router subsystem.
end note

[Ollama] as Ollama <<Local LLM — Last Resort Fallback Only>>
note bottom of Ollama
  Terminal fallback ONLY on quota exhaustion
  or budget cap. Never a preference.
  UI must indicate degraded mode prominently.
end note

interface "HTTP POST localhost:7777" as LocalAPI <<Primary Bridge>>
interface "MCP Protocol" as MCP <<External Data Layer Only>>

Neovim --> NvimPlugin : triggers commands
NvimPlugin --> ExistingPlugins : fallback when rust_agent_server unavailable
NvimPlugin --> LocalAPI : primary path — sends requests
ExistingPlugins ..> AG : auth/proxy (optional)
LocalAPI --> RustServer : delegates tasks
RustServer --> Gemini : cloud inference (primary)
RustServer ..> Ollama : fallback inference (last resort)
RustServer ..> MCP : external data only (filesystem, git, web, LSP)
AG .> RustServer : dev-time socket bridge

package "Collaboration Workflow (Principle 10)" {
  note "User: Implements Rust, reviews ALL code, sovereign approval\nAI Specialist: Designs logic, submits PRs — no merge authority\nBoth: Use Antigravity for research\nAll PRs = proposals until User explicitly approves" as CollabNote
}
CollabNote ..> RustServer
CollabNote ..> NvimPlugin

@enduml
